Resources for System Administrators

Explore the services catalog, Apex triggers, UI templates, and more.

Insurance Services Catalog
Get quote, policy, and claims systems up and running by using an extensive catalog of Digital Insurance Platform services.
Actionable Relationship Center (ARC) in Insurance
Actionable Relationship Center (ARC) lets you view your insurance customers' relationships in an easy-to-navigate graph.
Data Processing Engine Definitions for Insurance
Data Processing Engine helps you transform data thatâ€™s available in your Salesforce org and writes back the transformation results as new or updated records.
Einstein Generative AI for Insurance (Beta)
Bring the power of conversational AI to your insurance business with Einstein Copilot.
Insurance Policyholder Portal
With Experience Cloud, you can personalize the digital experience for your policyholders.
Insurance Service Excellence
Orchestrate every part of the service experience and provide meaningful, personalized interactions to your customers from a unified console.
Marketing Cloud Engagement for Insurance
Increase customer engagement by using Marketing Cloud Engagement for Insurance.
Invocable Actions in Insurance
Use these invocable actions in Insurance flows.
Insurance Apex Triggers
Depending on how you use Insurance, you might need to perform additional tasks after installation, such as creating and modifying Custom Settings.
Insurance FSC Unmanaged Package Experience Templates
Use Experience site templates and pre-built components to start creating your own Experience sites.
Insurance Industries Extension Integration
Enable the Insurance Industries Extension package and learn about a mapping interface that lets Vlocity policy services work with the Salesforce FSC Insurance Policy data model.
Insurance Lightning Web Component UI Reference
Insurance Lightning web components provide a layered framework that displays, processes, passes, retrieves, and re-displays data.
Insurance UI Template Catalog
Insurance UI templates work with OmniScripts to create an attractive end-user experience that integrates data such as rated products, insured items, available coverages, calculated prices, and coverage attributes.
Insurance and Financial Services Data Model
The Insurance and Financial Services data model is a comprehensive data model designed to address the complexities and challenges faced by cloud-based insurance and financial services systems across insurance markets.
